videos.description: Cincy's Jarron Cumberland works his way into the lane as he absorbs the contact.
videos.headline: Cumberland finishes floater for bucket

videos.description: After a missed 3-pointer by Landry Shamet, Cincy's Cane Broome grabs the rebound and takes it the length of the floor for a 2-point floater to tie the game.
videos.headline: Cincy's fast-break floater ties game

videos.description: Landry Shamet drives to the basket but gets stopped by Cincy's Kyle Washington, who denies the layup.
videos.headline: Washington stuffs Wichita State

videos.description: Cane Broome drives inside and finishes with an impressive move for two points while getting fouled.
videos.headline: Cincy's Broome gets crafty for and-1

videos.description: Conner Frankamp puts the moves on Cincinnati defenders and scoops it in to extend the Shockers' lead.
videos.headline: Wichita State's Frankamp puts the moves on for 2

videos.description: Rashard Kelly fakes out multiple defenders as he switches directions while going for a layup.
videos.headline: Kelly fakes out Cincy's D for and-1

videos.description: After a clutch Cincinnati steal, Gary Clark finds Tre Scott who slams it down to make it a one-possession game against Wichita State.
videos.headline: Critical steal leads to clutch Cincy bucket

videos.description: On consecutive possessions, Landry Shamet finds teammates Austin Reaves and Shaquille Morris who deliver key buckets to defeat Cincinnati.
videos.headline: Shockers clinch win with pair of late fast breaks

videos.description: Coach Gregg Marshall reflects on his team's hard-fought victory over Cincinnati and his players' ability to make plays when they needed to.
videos.headline: Marshall on Shockers: 'They want to play for a championship'
